15 (ii) On a second conviction, the person shall be fined an amount not to exceed $1,000 or be
16 imprisoned in the county jail for a term of not more than 1 year, or both.
17 (iii) On a third or subsequent conviction, the person shall be fined an amount not to exceed
18 $10,000 or be imprisoned in a state prison for a term of not more than 10 years, or both.
19 (c) As used in this subsection (4), "public place" means a place to which the public or a group of
20 persons has access and includes but is not limited to transportation facilities, restrooms, locker rooms, dressing
21 rooms, and showers that are designated for multiperson, single-sex use, schools, places of amusement, parks,
22 places of business, playgrounds, and hallways, lobbies, and other portions of apartment houses, multifamily
23 dwellings, and hotels, except for rooms or apartments designed for actual residence."
